          <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a></div>                              <h2>Dear Deceiver</h2>                                                  <div class="clear-block">
            <div id="node-50" class="node">



  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <p><img hspace="10" vspace="10" align="left" src="http://www.marynichols.co.uk/sites/default/files/Dear%20Deceiver_0.jpg" width="208" height="319" />DEAR DECEIVER<br />
No 25 in The Regency Lords &amp; Ladies Collection<br />
to be published by Mills &amp; Boon<br />
in large print January 2010<br />
ISBN: 978 0 263 21053 8<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<p>Dominic could be certain Emma had been lying to him. He wasn't even sure that Emma Woodhill was her real name. So why was he so attracted to her when he was already engaged to someone else? Still, Dominic was determined to discover the truth and give Emma all the help she needed&hellip;</p>
<p>This is a reprint of a story first published in 2007.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>  </div>

